abstract = {To combat and anticipate new diseases, health care delivery necessitates the use of new technologies such as the Internet of Things (IoT), and artificial intelligence (AI) is an innovative approach advancement that will be helpful against several health care deformities. We intend to examine the role of AI as well as the involvement of nanotechnology as a critical technology in assessing, preparing for, and combating the coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) pandemic. We obtained the most recent information on AI for COVID-19 and then assessed it to determine its potential application for this condition. Health care companies urgently require decision-making systems to handle this infection and assist them in receiving appropriate real-time recommendations to prevent its spread. AI and IoT work proficiently to replicate human intelligence. It may also play an important role in identifying and suggesting the creation of a COVID-19 vaccine. This chapter focuses on this outcome-driven technology, which is utilized for effective screening, evaluating, forecasting, and tracking of present and potential future patients. The significant applications track data from verified, recovered, and death cases.}
